snippet.textDisplay:
If I were you, I would obey my teacher, whether what she says makes sense :)
Fingering is completely dependent on our hand structure and size.

"...Be especially careful to choose the fingering which best suits your
hand and the phrasing of the passage. Good editions of music usually
have sensible fingerings, but if there is any department of piano
playing where you should follow your own judgment it is that of
fingering. The best teachers will always tell you that..." Charles
Cooke, Playing the Piano for Pleasure
